========================================================
PROMPT EXAMPLE — Option 2: Map One Node Per Call
========================================================

This file shows a concrete example of the prompt sent to the LLM under
Option 2 (option: 2 in LLM_mapping_RA.yml). In this mode, RAMD issues a
separate LLM call for each node in the graph (the "target node"), providing
only that node's neighbors as local context. This is the default and
best-performing mode in the paper.

The prompt is constructed by prompts.build_option2_prompt_for_node() and
includes:
  - The target node name
  - Names of its immediate neighbors in the AADL graph
  - RA component names with their textual descriptions (if use_ra_descriptions: true)
  - Few-shot examples drawn from the same RA domain (if fewshot_learning: true)
  - Constraint feedback from the previous iteration (if check_RA_constraints: true)
  - A task instruction specifying the required JSON output schema

------------------------------------------------------------
SYSTEM PROMPT
------------------------------------------------------------
You are an expert software architect and a careful classifier.
You will receive:
  (a) the name of a target node in an AADL graph,
  (b) the names of its neighbor nodes (if any), and
  (c) a finite set of reference architecture components as labels (as a list of names).
Select EXACTLY ONE best label for the target node and also return a ranked list
of labels with confidence scores in [0,1].
All labels in the output MUST be exactly one of the provided component names.
Return ONLY strict JSON with this schema:
{"best":"<label>", "ranked":[{"label":"<label>","score":0.0}, ...]}

